name        : linux-pam
version     : @LINUX_PAM_VERSION@
release     : 1
summary     : ONIX-owned Linux-PAM runtime surface
license     : BSD-3-Clause
homepage    : https://github.com/linux-pam/linux-pam
upstreams   :
    - @LINUX_PAM_PAYLOAD_URL@: @LINUX_PAM_PAYLOAD_SHA256@
description : |
    Linux-PAM shared-library and module surface for ONIX.

    This is an intentional dynamic-musl exception. PAM's useful runtime model is
    libpam plus loadable modules, so ONIX owns that surface as a stone instead
    of treating it as a host leak.

    Source archive: @LINUX_PAM_SOURCE_ARCHIVE@
    Source SHA-256: @LINUX_PAM_SOURCE_SHA256@
install     : |
    install -dm00755 %(installroot)
    cp -a usr %(installroot)/

    chmod 00755 %(installroot)/usr
    chmod 00755 %(installroot)/usr/lib
    chmod 00755 %(installroot)/usr/share
    chmod 00755 %(installroot)/usr/share/onix
    chmod 00755 %(installroot)/usr/share/onix/packages
    chmod 0644 %(installroot)/usr/share/onix/packages/linux-pam.md
